WEBVTT

01:34.929 --> 01:38.304
Do you, Alice,

01:38.339 --> 01:41.340
take Joseph...

01:41.375 --> 01:44.343
to be your husband

01:44.378 --> 01:48.842
in sickness and in health...

01:48.877 --> 01:52.846
until distance do you part?

01:55.224 --> 01:57.785
I do.

01:57.820 --> 02:00.722
And do you, Joseph,

02:00.757 --> 02:06.266
take Alice to be your wife...

02:06.301 --> 02:10.468
in sickness
and in health

02:10.503 --> 02:14.703
until distance do you part?

02:14.738 --> 02:16.507
I do.

02:18.775 --> 02:22.381
I now pronounce you...

02:22.416 --> 02:25.714
man and wife.

02:29.786 --> 02:31.489
Joseph!

02:31.524 --> 02:33.293
Joseph!

02:34.824 --> 02:36.593
Joseph!

02:48.035 --> 02:52.345
The Lord has decided
that he needed to test us.

02:52.380 --> 02:57.251
-Mr. Paul?
-The deed has been done.

02:59.013 --> 03:01.552
It wasn't a rabbit.

03:01.587 --> 03:04.357
You arrogance blinded you,
Joseph.

03:04.392 --> 03:06.920
We'll note it for Sunday.

03:09.023 --> 03:11.298
Now grab one end.

03:24.577 --> 03:27.710
He said,
"If you will diligently listen

03:27.745 --> 03:30.482
to the voice of the Lord,
your God,

03:30.517 --> 03:34.915
and do that
which is right in His eyes...

03:36.754 --> 03:40.789
...give ears to His commands
and keep all His statutes,

03:40.824 --> 03:43.561
I will put none
of the diseases on you

03:43.596 --> 03:45.431
that I put on the Egyptians...

03:47.600 --> 03:51.932
...for I am the Lord,
your healer."

04:08.984 --> 04:11.556
Mr. Paul.
Mr. Paul!

04:11.591 --> 04:12.722
Mr. Paul!
I caught a rat!

04:23.900 --> 04:26.472
Don't even think
about helping him up.

04:26.507 --> 04:28.001
He did this on his own.

04:28.036 --> 04:31.004
He can get up on his own.

04:43.755 --> 04:46.822
Y'all heard him.
Get back to work!

04:46.857 --> 04:48.791
Back to work.

04:51.433 --> 04:53.367
Back to work, boy.

05:04.413 --> 05:06.446
-Hold still.

05:13.950 --> 05:15.752
Ruthie?

05:15.787 --> 05:18.392
You can't be sneaking over here
and playing like this.

05:18.427 --> 05:19.954
As the oldest woman
in this bunch,

05:19.989 --> 05:22.154
I think I can do just about
anything I want to do.

05:22.189 --> 05:25.531
And right now,
I want to see my son.

05:29.966 --> 05:34.133
Best not to hear
those stories tonight, Alice.

05:34.168 --> 05:35.970
Her reading's
the only thing we got.

05:39.547 --> 05:42.449
We can't keep doing this.

05:42.484 --> 05:44.946
We thank keep letting Mr. Paul
do what he wants.

05:46.686 --> 05:48.950
It's a choice
we don't have to make.

05:48.985 --> 05:51.018
If any one of us
start acting up,

05:51.053 --> 05:52.756
you know what would happen?

05:52.791 --> 05:54.087
We'd all die.

05:56.190 --> 05:58.432
There's 12 of us.

05:58.467 --> 06:00.665
There's one of him.

06:00.700 --> 06:03.635
Three if you count
Mrs. Bennett and Mr. Aaron.

06:03.670 --> 06:06.132
Not all of us had the teaching
from Mr. Paul you had.

06:06.167 --> 06:07.738
How?

06:07.773 --> 06:10.741
The men that hunt runaways
work at night.

06:10.776 --> 06:13.106
We've all heard the stories.

06:13.141 --> 06:15.647
I ain't never heard of them
hunting in the day.

06:15.682 --> 06:17.077
It won't work, Alice.

06:17.112 --> 06:20.014
She ain't wrong
for thinking about it.

06:20.049 --> 06:23.655
None of us are.

06:23.690 --> 06:26.053
There's got to be
something else.

06:26.088 --> 06:28.957
A bunch of white men
out there waiting...

06:28.992 --> 06:32.059
to kill us, keep us, or sell us.

06:33.128 --> 06:34.930
I need to speak to my wife.

06:35.900 --> 06:37.504
Alone.

06:47.780 --> 06:50.110
-Joseph, this place --
-Paul knows.

06:51.212 --> 06:54.653
About us.

06:54.688 --> 06:56.787
About everything.

08:02.019 --> 08:04.085
No, my brothers and sisters!

08:04.120 --> 08:07.561
This was no messenger from God.

08:07.596 --> 08:11.224
This was a warning
from the devil himself.

08:14.834 --> 08:18.605
Even in our gracious state
of Georgia...

08:18.640 --> 08:21.168
on God-given land,

08:21.203 --> 08:24.875
the devil has ways
of sending an emissary.

08:26.879 --> 08:31.882
He said, "You must continue
to be fruitful.

08:33.688 --> 08:38.053
Not only for yourselves,
but for your domestic livestock,

08:38.088 --> 08:42.321
for they, too, must be bathed
in the bounty of birth.

08:44.798 --> 08:47.326
Or I will...

08:47.361 --> 08:51.198
take it all away."

09:11.792 --> 09:14.056
I need to have
a word with you.

09:36.014 --> 09:40.951
How long has it been
since we lost your beloved?

09:45.353 --> 09:47.287
Long time ago.

09:52.129 --> 09:55.097
I've always tried my best
to take care of you.

09:55.132 --> 09:56.769
Haven't I?

10:05.142 --> 10:07.373
You want to be inside.
Is that it?

10:11.214 --> 10:12.917
No, sir.

10:12.952 --> 10:14.721
A home life.

10:16.384 --> 10:19.286
This is what you're longing for,
isn't it?

10:19.321 --> 10:23.730
When your wife passed...
I should've married you off.

10:25.096 --> 10:28.394
Could have had sons
working by your side.

10:29.364 --> 10:31.001
Mr. Paul, I --

10:31.036 --> 10:32.739
Our neighbor, Brother Levi,

10:32.774 --> 10:36.171
has offered one of his domestics
to be your bride.

10:42.146 --> 10:44.245
I'm happy, Mr. Paul.

10:45.754 --> 10:48.788
I-I work hard.
I-I don't need --

10:48.823 --> 10:51.824
The message was clear.
You need to be fruitful.

10:51.859 --> 10:53.892
Along with
the other domestics.

10:53.927 --> 10:57.390
This -- This is a big thing
Brother Levi is doing for us.

10:58.833 --> 11:01.163
He hasn't been as blessed
with his domestics.

11:05.136 --> 11:07.268
We've agreed
that the first child

11:07.303 --> 11:10.403
will rightfully go to him.

11:12.946 --> 11:16.882
You'll leave this week to...

11:19.183 --> 11:21.150
...to procreate.

11:22.857 --> 11:25.055
And then, when the pregnancy
is confirmed,

11:25.090 --> 11:27.189
you can return.

11:38.565 --> 11:42.237
This is so much bigger
than -- than us.

11:57.925 --> 12:01.322
Daniel's coming home tomorrow.

12:01.357 --> 12:03.159
MRS.
And Rachel.

12:07.836 --> 12:10.529
She's been gone a long time now.

12:13.138 --> 12:15.435
Your mind's not
what it used to be, Mother.

12:27.383 --> 12:29.152
It's Sunday.

12:49.878 --> 12:51.273
I said it's Sunday.

12:57.050 --> 12:58.819
I know.

13:01.285 --> 13:02.515
You go on ahead of me.

13:06.323 --> 13:08.961
What about Mrs. Bennett?

13:10.657 --> 13:13.064
Ruth can put her to bed.

14:57.005 --> 14:59.269
Nobody said you could sit there.

15:18.026 --> 15:19.718
You think you look like this?

15:23.163 --> 15:25.196
I just looked at the picture.

15:25.231 --> 15:26.626
I didn't...

15:26.661 --> 15:30.201
You don't read good enough
to understand...

15:30.236 --> 15:32.500
the meaning, Alice.

15:35.439 --> 15:37.307
I-I only taught you

15:37.342 --> 15:41.410
so you could read to me
as a domestic.

15:41.445 --> 15:43.544
Understand?

15:46.120 --> 15:48.120
Understand?

15:48.155 --> 15:49.484
Yes.

15:49.519 --> 15:50.749
Good.

15:53.160 --> 15:54.390
Sit.

15:57.758 --> 15:59.362
On the bed.

16:39.107 --> 16:41.272
Have you ever thought
about running away?

16:42.008 --> 16:46.046
Pondering is only
gonna make you feel worse.

16:49.381 --> 16:51.480
Have you ever thought about it?

16:53.484 --> 16:55.286
We don't --
We don't talk about that.

16:55.321 --> 16:57.684
I didn't ask
if we talked about it.

16:57.719 --> 17:00.357
I asked you
if you thought about it.

17:06.167 --> 17:08.860
Used to.

17:08.895 --> 17:13.337
But I just chose
not to see things

17:13.372 --> 17:14.866
out of my control.

17:14.901 --> 17:18.738
That kind of thinking
will get you killed.

17:20.577 --> 17:23.512
You ever hear stories
about anyone making it out?

17:28.321 --> 17:29.749
Your granddaddy...

17:32.622 --> 17:36.723
...once said he -- he saw a man.

17:43.336 --> 17:45.336
One of us.

17:48.473 --> 17:50.341
As if...

17:50.376 --> 17:53.674
As if he just fell from the sky.

17:59.385 --> 18:01.847
Could start a fire
with his hands.

18:06.359 --> 18:08.128
Mm-hmm.

18:13.234 --> 18:15.399
He's still out there.

18:16.666 --> 18:19.403
My daddy...

18:19.438 --> 18:23.440
buried him over in that --
in that corral.

18:24.075 --> 18:29.182
Strangest-looking man
he'd ever seen.

18:30.977 --> 18:32.746
-Did you see him?
-Oh, no, I wasn't --

18:32.781 --> 18:34.781
I wasn't trying to.

19:39.045 --> 19:42.981
What are you doing?
What are you doing, son?

19:43.016 --> 19:44.884
What are you --

20:47.487 --> 20:49.751
We can fix those.

20:52.756 --> 20:54.624
You like your schoolin'?

20:57.398 --> 21:00.465
Well, I'll bet you have
a lot of friends.

21:00.500 --> 21:02.830
Not really.

21:02.865 --> 21:05.932
Well, you know what that means.

21:05.967 --> 21:08.000
You're a smarter person.

21:08.035 --> 21:11.476
They don't understand you.

21:11.511 --> 21:13.610
A man is rich
not by what he owns,

21:13.645 --> 21:15.843
but by what he can do without.

21:21.114 --> 21:22.850
Mrs. Bennett awake?

21:22.885 --> 21:25.358
Mm-hmm.
She's in the sitting room.

21:25.393 --> 21:27.987
Well, get her.
Her grandson's home.

21:29.991 --> 21:31.562
Hi, Mr. Daniel.

21:33.060 --> 21:34.697
Hi.

21:37.768 --> 21:40.505
You hungry?

21:40.540 --> 21:43.838
Make something
for me and my boy.

21:59.427 --> 22:01.526
Can't you see?

23:17.934 --> 23:19.967
Mrs. Bennett.

23:20.002 --> 23:21.705
Mrs. --

23:24.611 --> 23:26.105
I was a dancer, you know.

23:26.140 --> 23:28.613
In Chicago.

23:31.651 --> 23:34.553
Mrs. Bennett...

23:34.588 --> 23:36.522
what's out there?

23:36.557 --> 23:39.250
The whole world.

23:39.285 --> 23:41.758
Don't you see it?

24:06.884 --> 24:09.082
I found this.

24:09.117 --> 24:11.183
What is it?

24:11.218 --> 24:14.527
Something from somewhere.

24:14.562 --> 24:17.057
Someone from someplace.

24:17.928 --> 24:19.796
Who?

24:19.831 --> 24:21.996
Someone like us.

24:22.031 --> 24:24.933
There's more than we know...

24:24.968 --> 24:26.902
more than we can see.

24:29.973 --> 24:32.039
We have to go.

24:32.074 --> 24:33.876
-I don't know.
-We'll go.

24:33.911 --> 24:37.275
If we make it out,
we come back for everyone

24:37.310 --> 24:39.145
and burn this place
to the ground.

24:42.249 --> 24:44.018
Aaron's got a gun.

24:44.053 --> 24:46.185
You let me worry about that.

24:55.702 --> 24:57.570
What if...

24:59.838 --> 25:02.641
What if there's nothing
out there?

25:03.644 --> 25:06.073
I'll take my chances.

25:07.241 --> 25:09.175
Will you?

25:11.751 --> 25:13.146
Yes.

25:15.150 --> 25:17.084
Wait for my signal.

25:26.293 --> 25:28.161
"There's a strange land yonder,

25:28.196 --> 25:33.067
a land of witchcraft
and beautiful things,

25:33.102 --> 25:36.235
a land of brave people."

25:46.082 --> 25:47.818
-I got this, Daddy.
-Hmm?

25:48.689 --> 25:50.854
"What is the good of..."

25:51.989 --> 25:55.386
"What is the good of talking?

25:55.421 --> 25:58.323
It grows dark.

25:58.358 --> 26:02.129
Those who live to see will see.

26:02.164 --> 26:05.770
'You need not fear me,
Macumazahn,'

26:05.805 --> 26:08.773
he said, interpreting my look."

26:12.009 --> 26:13.338
Mr. Aaron!

26:16.882 --> 26:20.279
"I dig no holes
for you to fall in,

26:20.314 --> 26:21.687
I make no plots."

26:21.722 --> 26:23.084
You're crazy!

26:23.119 --> 26:25.251
-What you want, boy?
-I caught a rabbit.

26:25.519 --> 26:28.892
Oh.
Well...show me.

26:31.798 --> 26:34.293
-"I-If we..."

26:37.298 --> 26:41.201
"If ever we are..."

26:41.236 --> 26:43.841
Get inside.
Keep reading.

26:54.722 --> 26:56.821
-No!

26:58.858 --> 27:00.187
Go! Go!

27:00.222 --> 27:02.024
Go! Run!

27:02.059 --> 27:04.092
Go! Run! Go!

27:04.127 --> 27:05.456
Don't stop!
Don't stop!

27:05.491 --> 27:06.897
Go!

27:06.932 --> 27:08.800
-Go! Go!

27:08.835 --> 27:10.065
Run!

27:10.100 --> 27:13.167
Run! Go!
Run!

27:13.202 --> 27:15.070
Go!

27:28.085 --> 27:30.118
Mr. Paul!

27:30.153 --> 27:32.252
I got him, Mr. Paul!

27:45.399 --> 27:48.136
Mr. Paul!

27:48.171 --> 27:50.171
Mr. Paul, I got him!

27:50.206 --> 27:53.108
I got him!
I got him!

27:53.143 --> 27:55.880
Mr. Paul.
Mr. Paul!

27:55.915 --> 27:59.246
I got him!
I got him! I got him!

28:04.121 --> 28:05.989
I think he's gone.

28:08.422 --> 28:11.324
All I ever tried to do...

28:11.359 --> 28:15.130
was protect you.

28:15.165 --> 28:17.396
Now, you go look.

28:18.399 --> 28:20.267
You go look...

28:20.302 --> 28:26.471
and you see
what betrayal looks like.

28:26.506 --> 28:28.209
You go look!

28:48.099 --> 28:51.397
What do you say I have Moses
make you some new toys?

28:51.432 --> 28:53.806
I want to go home.

29:44.056 --> 29:47.090
Alice, I want you
to sit with us.

29:50.997 --> 29:52.931
Sit!

30:00.039 --> 30:02.138
Looks good.
Don't you think, Daniel?

30:10.247 --> 30:11.950
Mm.

30:11.985 --> 30:14.249
Alice is a good cook.

30:29.662 --> 30:32.234
Be a shame to lose her.

30:56.161 --> 30:58.326
Stop!

30:58.361 --> 30:59.624
Shut your mouth!

30:59.659 --> 31:02.495
-Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

31:03.729 --> 31:06.301
Stop! Stop! Stop!

31:08.569 --> 31:11.471
Stop! Stop! Stop!

31:32.758 --> 31:34.362
Help me!

31:38.170 --> 31:39.433
Use the scold's bridle.

31:39.468 --> 31:40.401
No!

31:40.436 --> 31:42.469
No! No! No! No!

31:42.504 --> 31:44.075
No!

31:44.110 --> 31:45.978
You stop!

31:46.013 --> 31:47.111
Stop!

31:47.146 --> 31:50.180
What did I do to deserve this?!

31:50.215 --> 31:52.281
What did I do?!

31:55.187 --> 31:57.187
I really liked you, Alice.

31:57.222 --> 31:58.650
I really liked you!

32:02.161 --> 32:03.490
No!

34:30.441 --> 34:33.211
I want to move past this, Alice.

34:49.658 --> 34:52.395
The greatest gift
God gave to man

34:52.430 --> 34:54.364
was forgiveness.

37:24.615 --> 37:26.648
Aah!

38:03.687 --> 38:04.851
Miss?

38:04.886 --> 38:05.984
Miss?

38:06.019 --> 38:07.557
Miss, can you hear me?

38:07.592 --> 38:09.460
Miss? Miss, you got --

38:09.495 --> 38:10.758
Miss --

38:10.793 --> 38:11.957
Be cool, man!

38:11.992 --> 38:13.530
Miss?!

38:13.565 --> 38:15.763
Miss?

38:15.798 --> 38:17.732
Miss...

38:25.610 --> 38:27.478
<i>Don't give him no peace sign</i>

38:27.513 --> 38:29.711
<i>If you don't mean it</i>
<i>from your heart</i>

38:29.746 --> 38:31.944
<i>-United we can get over</i>
-United we can get over

38:31.979 --> 38:34.012
<i>-But yet were still apart</i>
-But yet were still apart

38:34.047 --> 38:38.555
<i>'Cause each man demands respect</i>
<i>and to get an equal share</i>

38:38.590 --> 38:40.084
<i>And until</i>
<i>you're givin' him that</i>

38:40.119 --> 38:42.691
<i>There'll be no peace</i>

38:42.726 --> 38:44.396
<i>Brother's gonna work it out</i>

38:44.431 --> 38:46.024
<i>Brother's gonna work it out</i>

38:46.059 --> 38:48.796
<i>Brother's gonna work it out</i>

38:48.831 --> 38:49.995
<i>Brother's gonna work it out</i>

38:50.030 --> 38:53.636
<i>Oh, we must all join hands</i>

38:53.671 --> 38:55.968
<i>We can march across</i>
<i>this land in peace...</i>

38:58.775 --> 39:00.643
Be cool!
Be cool.

39:00.678 --> 39:01.776
Listen.
Be cool.

39:04.748 --> 39:06.649
Be cool.
Ma'am...

39:06.684 --> 39:07.815
-Be cool.

39:07.850 --> 39:11.555
Be cool. Hey.
Hey, relax.

39:11.590 --> 39:13.150
Do you remember?
You fainted.

39:13.185 --> 39:16.626
I couldn't leave you out there.

39:16.661 --> 39:19.024
How did you get free?

39:19.059 --> 39:21.191
<i>When reality's all gone?</i>

39:21.226 --> 39:23.468
Free?

39:23.503 --> 39:25.569
What is this?!

39:25.604 --> 39:26.867
Hey, hey.
Hey!

39:26.902 --> 39:28.198
Don't -- Don't touch that.

39:28.233 --> 39:29.738
No, don't -- don't --

39:29.773 --> 39:32.609
Hold up, now.
Don't touch that door.

39:32.644 --> 39:35.876
You must've hit your head
real hard.

39:35.911 --> 39:37.449
<i>Eyes to the facts</i>

39:37.484 --> 39:39.517
<i>Of what's truly</i>
<i>holding you back</i>

39:39.552 --> 39:43.455
<i>Ooh, ooh, ooh</i>

39:43.490 --> 39:47.217
Do you --
Do you know you in George?

39:47.252 --> 39:50.693
You do?

39:50.728 --> 39:53.960
Do you know it's 1973.

39:53.995 --> 39:57.469
<i>Oh, right on</i>

39:57.504 --> 39:59.933
As far as I'm concerned,
we went back 10 years

39:59.968 --> 40:02.540
with that jive ass
Nixon in office.

40:02.575 --> 40:04.938
You can go back?

40:04.973 --> 40:06.511
Oh, nah.

40:06.546 --> 40:08.480
Hell,
that would be slick.

40:15.687 --> 40:18.754
Air Force?

40:18.789 --> 40:22.186
Say,
that's an old Zippo.

40:22.221 --> 40:23.924
You know
what this is?

40:23.959 --> 40:26.157
Yeah, it's a lighter.
Let me see it.

40:26.192 --> 40:28.599
<i>Yet you stay locked</i>
<i>behind defeat</i>

40:28.634 --> 40:31.162
<i>Yet the key is</i>
<i>in your mind</i>

40:31.197 --> 40:32.570
Johnson?

40:32.605 --> 40:33.934
That your family?

40:33.969 --> 40:36.937
Uh, I have to get
out of this --

40:40.074 --> 40:42.811
Miss, there's napkins
in that glove compartment.

40:44.914 --> 40:46.782
There's napkins there.
Get the napkin--

40:56.563 --> 40:57.859
I'm sorry.

40:57.894 --> 40:59.223
I didn't m-mean to.

41:00.259 --> 41:01.863
It's okay.

41:03.702 --> 41:05.966
It's all right.
It's okay.

41:12.106 --> 41:15.008
I'm gonna let you
off up the ways.

41:15.043 --> 41:18.748
There's a hospital
right up there.

41:18.783 --> 41:20.651
They can
take care of you.

41:45.810 --> 41:47.612
Come on.

41:47.647 --> 41:49.746
I can't leave
this truck here.

41:52.850 --> 41:55.587
The people inside,
they're gonna help you.

42:12.067 --> 42:13.770
Excuse me.

42:13.805 --> 42:15.739
I picked up this woman
on the highway.

42:15.774 --> 42:17.708
-She fell.
-Okay.

42:17.743 --> 42:21.173
She might have amnesia. I
don't know.

42:21.208 --> 42:23.241
